Sentencas: Operation of solid oxide fuel/electrolysis cells (SOFC/SOEC) at high temperatures (T > 850 degrees C) is accompanied by degradation phenomena, which severely affect the operational lifetime of the cell.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes

Sentencas: Degradation processes are expected to occur slower at low temperatures.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes

Sentencas: However, significant reduction in electrocatalytic activity of the oxygen electrode, is one of the major challenges in decreasing the operating temperature down to 500 degrees C-650 degrees C. Recently, Pr6O11 infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 (CGO) based electrodes have been proposed to realize high electrochemical performance at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes

Sentencas: In this study, Pr-oxide has been infiltrated into a well performing sub-micro La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 (LSCF/CGO) composite electrode as well as a poorly performing LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 (LNF/CGO) electrode.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes

Sentencas: The results are compared with Cu-oxide infiltration.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes

Sentencas: Formation of Pr rich oxide surface nanostructures, resulted in a pronounced reduction of polarization resistances by a factor of 3 in state of the art LSCF/CGO electrodes.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes

Sentencas: Even better performances were achieved in Pr6O11 infiltrated LNF/CGO, demonstrating low polarization resistances of 0.074 +/- 0.002 and 0.146 +/- 0.002 Omega.cm(2) at 600 degrees C and 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes

Sentencas: Low degradation rates were observed over a 200 h durability test at 650 degrees C, illustrating the potential of Pr6O11 infiltrated CGO oxygen electrodes for intermediate temperature SOFC/SOEC application.
Titulo: Enhanced Activity of Pr6O11 and CuO Infiltrated Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 Based Composite Oxygen Electrodes
